uve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:11;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:12;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:13;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:14;s:58:"The garage door opener has a safety feature built into it.";i:15;s:79:"If it senses an obstruction while closing it will reverse to the open position.";i:16;s:69:"You have two adjustments for this feature down travel and down force.";i:17;s:85:"If the door is closing completely then reversing your down travel is adjusted to low.";i:18;s:111:"My garage door has two sensors either of which can cause the door to open immediately after apparently closing.";i:19;s:176:"A force-sensitive switch that detects if the motor torque is excessive typically tripped by incorrect adjustment or by leaving a solid object in the way of the descending door.";i:20;s:38:"My garage door wont close all the way.";i:21;s:46:"It goes part of the way down and then back up.";i:22;s:104:"Sometimes it doesnt go down much at all and sometimes it goes almost half way down before going back up.";i:23;s:80:"There is nothing between the sensors that would cause it to trigger then sensor.";i:24;s:78:"A faulty logic board could also be a reason your garage door opens then stops.";i:25;s:81:"This board electrically controls your garage door and will fail if it shorts out.";i:26;s:86:"Depending on how old your garage door opener is you may want to replace it if its old.";i:27;s:111:"When the door is in any position other than closed and the garage door opener is activated the door will close.";i:28;s:144:"If the garage door makes contact with an obstruction while closing the door will reverse the opener will beep and the lights will flash 5 times.";i:29;s:59:"Get shopping advice from experts friends and the community.";i:30;s:73:"When I open my garage door it opens all the way and then starts to close.";i:31;s:47:"Sort of like a bad brake or maybe a bad