ening and when it is closing.";i:55;s:51:"Do this with the door in the fully closed position.";i:56;s:45:"With the door closed and disengaged from the.";i:57;s:37:"Opener manually lift the garage door.";i:58;s:67:"If the door is very heavy then you have a spring that is broken or.";i:59;s:60:"In this case call a service company to replace the spring s.";i:60;s:78:"Sometimes there could be a box or a garbage can sitting too close to the eyes.";i:61;s:73:"Other times it may be a leaf hanging from the bottom of your garage door.";i:62;s:141:"Look at the photo eyes themselves if there are cobwebs or if there is dust on the lenses the eyes will sense this and cause the door reverse.";}}